commit.message: Updated doc, added info for Spark 3.0.
Updated version dependency for Spark to 2.4.5

Added configuration: spark.sparkmeasure.influxdbEnableBatch, boolean, default true
   Note: this may improve performance, but requires explicitly stopping Spark Sesssion: spark.stop()
Collect info on map executorId, executorHost with the InfluxDB sink.
Collect info on map executorId, executorHost with the InfluxDB sink.

The approach is to deliver a Scala Map rather than a JSON object.  (#26)

* The approach is to deliver a Scala Map rather than a JSON object.  This
allows the user to produce any number of outputs from the Map object
including JSON, CSV, XML or other format.  The user can also modify (ad
information to the map object).

The use case becomes:

1) user does sparkMeasure
val df :DataFrame =
stageMetrics.runAndMeasure(fillDataFrame(spark,format,
connectionProperties, query))

2) user calls reportMap() to get the map
stageMetrics.reportMap()

3) User is able to manipulate the map:
    map.put("id", "2")
    map.put("event", "queryStructure")
    map.put("queryName", name)

4) User converts map to desired output:
val msg = new org.apache.logging.log4j.message.ObjectMessage(map)
